      • setCameraResolution

        public CameraConfig.Builder setCameraResolution(int resolution)
        Set the resolution of the output camera image. If you don't specify any resolution, default image resolution will set to CameraResolution.MEDIUM_RESOLUTION.
        Parameters:
        resolution - Any resolution from:
      • CameraResolution.HIGH_RESOLUTION
      • CameraResolution.MEDIUM_RESOLUTION
      • CameraResolution.LOW_RESOLUTION
        • Returns:
        CameraConfig.Builder
        See Also:
        CameraResolution

      • setCameraFacing

        public CameraConfig.Builder setCameraFacing(int cameraFacing)
        Set the camera facing with which you want to capture image. Either rear facing camera or front facing camera. If you don't provide any camera facing, default camera facing will be CameraFacing.FRONT_FACING_CAMERA.
        Parameters:
        cameraFacing - Any camera facing from:
      • CameraFacing.REAR_FACING_CAMERA
      • CameraFacing.FRONT_FACING_CAMERA
        • Returns:
        CameraConfig.Builder
        See Also:
        CameraFacing

      • setCameraFocus

        public CameraConfig.Builder setCameraFocus(int focusMode)
        Set the camera focus mode. If you don't provide any camera focus mode, default focus mode will be CameraFocus.AUTO.
        Parameters:
        focusMode - Any camera focus mode from:
      • CameraFocus.AUTO
      • CameraFocus.CONTINUOUS_PICTURE
      • CameraFocus.NO_FOCUS
        • Returns:
        CameraConfig.Builder
        See Also:
        CameraFacing

      • setImageFormat

        public CameraConfig.Builder setImageFormat(int imageFormat)
        Specify the image format for the output image. If you don't specify any output format, default output format will be CameraImageFormat.FORMAT_JPEG.
        Parameters:
        imageFormat - Any supported image format from:
      • CameraImageFormat.FORMAT_JPEG
      • CameraImageFormat.FORMAT_PNG
        • Returns:
        CameraConfig.Builder
        See Also:
        CameraImageFormat

      • setImageRotation

        public CameraConfig.Builder setImageRotation(int rotation)
        Specify the output image rotation. The output image will be rotated by amount of degree specified before stored to the output file. By default there is no rotation applied.
        Parameters:
        rotation - Any supported rotation from:
      • CameraRotation.ROTATION_0
      • CameraRotation.ROTATION_90
      • CameraRotation.ROTATION_180
      • CameraRotation.ROTATION_270
        • Returns:
        CameraConfig.Builder
        See Also:
        CameraRotation

      • setImageFile

        public CameraConfig.Builder setImageFile(java.io.File imageFile)
        Set the location of the out put image. If you do not set any file for the output image, by default image will be stored in the application's cache directory.
        Parameters:
        imageFile - File where you want to store the image.
        Returns:
        CameraConfig.Builder

      • build

        public CameraConfig build()
        Build the configuration.
        Returns:
        CameraConfig

      • getDefaultStorageFile

        @NonNull
private java.io.File getDefaultStorageFile()
        Get the new file to store the image if there isn't any custom file location available. This will create new file into the cache directory of the application.
